{
  "texts": [
    "For fair comparison, we reuse evaluation metrics of previous works for regular and irregular settings [6], [7].ii) Discriminative Score: In order to assess how similar the original and generated samples are, we train a 2-layer LSTM model that classifies the real/fake samples into two classes, real or fake.",
    "We use the performance of the trained classifier on the test data as the discriminative score.",
    "Therefore, lower discriminator scores mean real and fake samples are similar.",
    "B. Hyperparameters and Miscellaneous EnvironmentsM θ has various hyperparameters and for key hyperparameters, we set them as listed in Table VI.",
    "For other common hyperparameters with baselines, we reuse the default configurations of TimeGAN [6] and VPSDE [17] to conduct the regular time-series generation."
  ]
}